solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int numberOfSpecialChars(string word) {
        int lower[26] = {0};
        int upper[26] = {0};
        for (char c : word) {
            if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') {
                lower[c - 'a']++;
            } else {
                upper[c - 'A']++;
            }
        }
        int res = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < 26; ++i) {
            if (lower[i] && upper[i]) {
                bool ok = true;
                bool seenUpper = false;
                for (char c : word) {
                    if (c == 'A' + i) {
                        seenUpper = true;
                    } else if (c == 'a' + i && seenUpper) {
                        ok = false;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if (ok) res++;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(26 * N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Count occurrences of each letter in both cases. For each letter that appears in both cases, scan the string once to verify every lowercase instance appears before the first uppercase instance.

